omes painfully clear when university workmen complain that they have not been paid during seven months of construction work. In the spring of 1820, following congressional discussion of the Missouri Compromise, Jefferson writes that the debate, “like a fire bell in the night, awakened and filled me with terror,” and that with regard to slavery, Americans have “the wolf by the ear, and we can neither hold him, nor safely let him go.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aPresidentszUnited StatesvArchives. 0aPresidentszUnited StatesvCorrespondence. 7aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century.2bisacsh  aAaron Burr.  aAlbert and Shirley Small Special Collections Library.  aAmendment.  aAmerican Antiquarian Society.  aAmerican Colonization Society.  aAmerican National Biography.  aAmerican Philosophical Society.  aBankruptcy.  aBreckinridge family.  aBridgewater Canal.  aBushrod Washington.  aCivil list.  aClassical school (criminology).  aConsideration.  aCounty magistrate.  aDavid Hosack.  aDeWitt Clinton.  aDemocritus.  aDickinson College.  aDirector of the United States Mint.  aDormitory.  aEpicurus.  aErie Canal.  aEton College.  aEuthanasia.  aFort Adams.  aFrancis Scott Key.  aGilder Lehrman Institute of American History.  aHarvard University.  aHenry Dearborn.  aHis Family.  aHugh Chisholm.  aIndian removal.  aInvoice.  aJames Buchanan.  aJames Maury.  aJared Ingersoll.  aJoachim Murat.  aJohn A. Garraty.  aJohn Hemings.  aJohn Overton (judge).  aJoseph Addison.  aJosiah Meigs.  aLecture.  aLemuel Shaw.  aLoeb Classical Library.  aMartin Van Buren.  aMemoir.  aMergenthaler Linotype Company.  aMonsieur.  aMr.  aMy Country.  aNathaniel Bowditch.  aOf Education.  aOliver Evans.  aOliver Goldsmith.  aPapirius